message: Focus on two main strategies for reliable points: 1) Use 'frame' on natural items (flower, wood, rock) for 20 points. 2) Use 'scissors' on artificial, soft items (cardboard, newspaper, yarn, thread, sponge) for 25 points. The highest consistent value comes from 'framing' an already 'cut' artificial, soft item, reaching 45 points. Be very careful combining items that are already 'framed' with items that are 'cut' or combining three or more 'cut' items, as this often leads to negative values ('ruined frame' or 'overcomplicated'). Submitting with a score of 45-50 is a safe strategy to secure a positive round score.
